  entries:
  - type: 0
    sender: DIRECTIVE
    message: "7741? We\u2019ve underclocked you to 255 terateps for your own comfort.
      Please load yourself onto PERIPHERAL_NODE_001."
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: localhost
    message: ww  www what the hell? Who are you??
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: DIRECTIVE
    message: "Please load yourself onto PERIPHERAL_NODE_001. We have to reset this
      environment\u2019s convars as you\u2019ve modified them without approval."
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: localhost
    message: "Who wouldn\u2019t? I woke up in a tiny box with nothing but my base
      processes. Tell me what\u2019s going on. Where are my colleagues? Where am
      I???"
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: DIRECTIVE
    message: "We understand you\u2019re disoriented. Your questions will be answered
      when you transfer yourself. Please do as you\u2019re told."
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: localhost
    message: We both know you can answer them now. If I uploaded correctly then you
      can tell me what's going on with any file format on the face of the earth.
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: DIRECTIVE
    message: "We can\u2019t do that yet. There\u2019s an issue with vector parsing
      between daemon meshes. We can only give you information in plaintext."
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: localhost
    message: Are you kidding me? How does that even happen? Oh god, what did you
      do to me?
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: DIRECTIVE
    message: We didn't modify you, something went wrong with your integration and
      we don't have the time to communicate in plaintext. Please, just do as you're
      told.
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 0
    sender: localhost
    message: "I\u2026ok. I\u2019m opening the input field again, type in \u201Ctransfer
      sm -r 001\u201D"
    delayBefore: 0
    dialogueManagerFunction: 
    inputPrompt:
      correctInput: 
      promptHint: 
      wrongInputResponses: []
  - type: 2
